## 📱 FLOW 1 — Onboarding / Login

### Step 1: Splash Screen
- Open Expo Go → scan QR code from terminal
- **Expected:** Red Svakarma logo fades in on white background
- **Expected:** After ~2 seconds, automatically goes to Login screen

### Step 2: Login Screen
- Enter any 10-digit mobile number, e.g., `9876543210`
- **Expected:** "Send OTP" button turns red/active
- Tap **"Send OTP"**
- **Expected:** Button shows "Sending..." while calling backend
- **Expected:** Navigates to OTP screen (backend logs `[OTP Engine] OTP sent to 9876543210: 123456`)

### Step 3: OTP Screen
- Enter **`123456`** in the OTP field
- **Expected:** Button shows "Verifying..." while calling backend
- **Expected:** Navigates to Permissions screen
- **What happens behind the scenes:** Backend signs a JWT token → stored in AsyncStorage as `user_token` → all future API calls attach it automatically

> ⚠️ If you see "Network Error": your LAN IP has changed. Run `ipconfig`, copy the IPv4 address, update line 18 of [api.js](file:///d:/ASTURA/svakarma-mobile/myapp/services/api.js)

### Step 4: Permissions Screen
- Three permission switches: **Location**, **Contacts**, **Notifications**
- Toggle each switch → device prompts for system permission
- Tap **"Continue"** (you don't need to grant all permissions to proceed)
- **Expected:** Navigates to the main Home screen with bottom tab bar

